Subject: [PATCH] uapi: random: include linux/types for __u32

After hiding the legacy typedefs from user land, <linux/random.h> no
longer gets __u32 implicitly, so BusyBox's seedrng.c fails to build.
Modern kernels explicitly include <linux/types.h> in this header; do the
same here so the struct definitions keep working for user space without
re-exposing the old typedef block.
---
 include/linux/random.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/include/linux/random.h
+++ b/include/linux/random.h
@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@
 #ifndef _LINUX_RANDOM_H
 #define _LINUX_RANDOM_H
 
+#include <linux/types.h>
 #include <linux/ioctl.h>
 
 /* ioctl()'s for the random number generator */
